Two suspects were on Thursday evening arrested for issuing fake Covid-19 clearance certificates in Busia county. The duo, 33-year- old Edward Okuku Alando and 32- year-old Yahya Ismael Sian were nabbed by DCI sleuths following concerns from the public. According to a statement by the Directorate of Criminal Investigation, several fake certificates have been confiscated from the suspects. "Additional items that include a computer and a scanner believed to have been used in running the fake Covid-19 testing centre were also recovered and have been retained as exhibits," the DCI said. "The two suspects are in lawful custody awaiting arraignment as search for a third individual namely Mark Ouma, believed to be the mastermind behind the syndicate continues."